			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Armor check please! <a name="69755"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 15 04 2:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When I made Calli 4 years ago I had no money and decided never to buy her armor.  She was going to loot every item she ever wore after killing mobs with her own hands.  So I still haven't bought armor in the bazaar which means I have no basis for pricing.  I just wanted to give you that heads up in case you look at my suggestions and say, &quot;WTF!  I told her 10k!&quot;  I'm a tradeskiller too, so I know about more tradeskilled items than anything else.
<br />

<br />
Upgrade Shopping List
<br />

<br />
Do Arms, Bracers, and Legs first!
<br />

<br />
<b>Arms</b> - This should be your first priority to upgrade
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68380">Dried Clay Armguards</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=72134">Magnetic Vambraces</a> (Charged Magnetic are better but more expensive)
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=62167">Light Chain Vambraces of Defeat</a>
<br />
Any of the elemental smithed armrs (Farwater Plate Vambraces, Livestone Plate Vambraces)
<br />

<br />
<b>Bracers</b>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=62151">Mark of the Victor</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=72132">Magnetic Vambraces</a> (Charged Magnetic are better but more expensive)
<br />
I am not sure who you worship, but you should also consider the deity-specific smithed armors.  (Tunare - Blessed Full Mithril Bracer, Rallos Zek - Fierce Heraldic Bracer, etc.)
<br />

<br />
<b>Legs</b>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=27777">Tae Ew Plate Greaves</a>
<br />
<a target="_new" href="Etched Greaves of Dark Might">Etched Greaves of Dark Might</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68400">Hardened Serpent-Scale Greaves</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=72115">Magnetic Leggings</a> (again, Charged Magnetic are better but more expensive, see note below)
<br />
Bloodstained Dragorn Greaves
<br />

<br />
Then if you have more to spend...
<br />

<br />
<b>Ears</b> to replace Boar Snout Ring
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=29047">Bloodmetal Earring of Engagement</a>
<br />

<br />
<b>Finger</b> to replace Darkwater Pearl Ring
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70119">Band of the Dark Betrayal</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=40150">Lavastone Ring</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=40163">Platinum Band of Savagery</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70094">Ring of 
<br />
Bonding</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68348">Stone Crested Ring</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=62166">Ring of Exalted Freedom</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=65531">Shadowbone Ring</a>
<br />

<br />
<b>Range</b> 
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70121">Blazing Fire Crystal</a>]
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=29031">Ceramic Incense Burner of Ro</a>
<br />

<br />
A few tips:
<br />

<br />
* If you're interested in tradeskilled items but they're too steep for your budget, see if you can get to know a tradeskiller who is working up another skill but already maxxed in the one you need.  For instance, if you find a friendly 250 smith who is still working on tailoring, you can probably barter tailoring components for a discount on smithed items.  I generally offer that option.
<br />

<br />
* Do LDoNs!  You can quite a few notable upgrades to your gear with LDoN points.  While you're in the missions, be sure to forage.  The foraged items are used to skill up smithing and can be used to entice someone who is maybe 250 in jewelery or pottery but still working on smithing.  You also tend to make money with every mission.
<br />

<br />
* Consider getting xp in Droga and doing those quests.  There are nice upgrades and a lot of the quest components are droppable and sold cheaply in the bazaar.</span></td>
